The paper discusses Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and their ability to encode position information. This topic is most closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) as CNNs are commonly used in image recognition tasks. Additionally, the paper discusses the learning of weights and filters, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments conducted in the paper involve training and testing neural networks, which is also a common topic in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the representation of information in deep CNNs, which is a topic in natural language processing (cs.CL).
